produces a unique situation

01:05:08.280 --> 01:05:13.710
which we will examine more
carefully later in this class.

01:05:13.710 --> 01:05:17.340
But could Manhattan be developed
on a different principle

01:05:17.340 --> 01:05:18.150
than a grid?

01:05:21.350 --> 01:05:23.600
That's asking a big question.

01:05:23.600 --> 01:05:26.490
We'd have to do
different plans for that

01:05:26.490 --> 01:05:31.130
and try to assemble the
conjecture that follows.

01:05:31.130 --> 01:05:34.940
We're not doing it, and
it's ridiculous to do it.

01:05:34.940 --> 01:05:37.010
The lessons from
Manhattan are to be

01:05:37.010 --> 01:05:41.870
learned by virtue of
reading the original plan

01:05:41.870 --> 01:05:45.050
and studying the
attempts to modify it.

01:05:47.750 --> 01:05:52.850
It like many-- how are we doing?

01:05:52.850 --> 01:05:58.700
Two minutes-- like
many city plans,

01:05:58.700 --> 01:06:01.130
is in a constant
state of adaptation.

01:06:05.270 --> 01:06:08.800
The Second Avenue
Subway is the last

01:06:08.800 --> 01:06:13.160
of the most recent of
the distortions of--

01:06:13.160 --> 01:06:16.580
not the distortions,
that adaptations

01:06:16.580 --> 01:06:20.210
to the plan, the attempt to--

01:06:22.850 --> 01:06:27.710
Rowe Price Manhattan
failed, it's probably

01:06:27.710 --> 01:06:31.660
likely to occur at sometime.

01:06:31.660 --> 01:06:37.490
The impossibility of connecting
the hinterland to the center

01:06:37.490 --> 01:06:41.600
is evidenced by the
fact that New York, one

01:06:41.600 --> 01:06:44.660
of the primary commercial
cities of the world,

01:06:44.660 --> 01:06:51.770
has the worst international
airport system of any city

01:06:51.770 --> 01:06:53.870
competitively.

01:06:53.870 --> 01:06:56.360
It's only the
arrogance of New York

01:06:56.360 --> 01:07:00.090
that let's it get away with
having a second rate airport

01:07:00.090 --> 01:07:00.590
system.

01:07:04.874 --> 01:07:10.670
Those of who have experienced
LaGuardia and Kennedy and New

01:07:10.670 --> 01:07:15.590
Jersey and have been
to great, new airports

01:07:15.590 --> 01:07:19.130
can argue for yourselves
the distinction.

01:07:22.850 --> 01:07:26.600
Carnegie Hall is one of the
most uncomfortable places

01:07:26.600 --> 01:07:28.820
to listen to great music.

01:07:28.820 --> 01:07:32.570
Again, New York gets
away through a kind

01:07:32.570 --> 01:07:34.890
of economic arrogance.

01:07:34.890 --> 01:07:39.230
The theory, which is highly
personal to me, that is,

01:07:39.230 --> 01:07:42.830
if you develop enough
economic strength,

01:07:42.830 --> 01:07:49.040
you need not follow it by
making everything of the highest

01:07:49.040 --> 01:07:51.520
order.

01:07:51.520 --> 01:07:54.670
It's a stupid phenomenon,
but maybe it's true.

01:07:54.670 --> 01:07:58.600
It's only in China, which
has new wealth, that people

01:07:58.600 --> 01:08:02.570
can build new airports.

01:08:02.570 --> 01:08:05.280
It's of course not totally true.

01:08:05.280 --> 01:08:13.700
But one of the major concerns
about the additive quality

01:08:13.700 --> 01:08:20.210
of the Chinese city is that
it is a city of addition

01:08:20.210 --> 01:08:25.550
and has lost any of the
attributes of the cosmos

01:08:25.550 --> 01:08:30.529
or even the Roman camp.

01:08:30.529 --> 01:08:32.960
We will go into that some more.

01:08:32.960 --> 01:08:35.240
The last group of
slides will deal

01:08:35.240 --> 01:08:41.840
with the evocation of linearity
and more modern concepts

01:08:41.840 --> 01:08:45.350
of the use of the
idea of the machine.

01:08:45.350 --> 01:08:48.649
So why don't we look at them,
otherwise we will just go on.

01:08:48.649 --> 01:08:50.000
This is a long class.

01:08:50.000 --> 01:08:51.980
This is an enormous
amount of stuff.

01:08:57.640 --> 01:09:01.689
I don't apologize for
these first three classes.

01:09:01.689 --> 01:09:05.229
Most you haven't done
enough urban history.

01:09:05.229 --> 01:09:06.670
Here are two examples.

01:09:06.670 --> 01:09:09.720
The one on the right
is from Tell el-Armana.

01:09:09.720 --> 01:09:21.100
The one on the left is from
Kahun 2460 BC and 320 BC.

01:09:21.100 --> 01:09:21.600
Next.

01:09:25.649 --> 01:09:28.080
This is the town
of Tell el-Amarna

01:09:28.080 --> 01:09:32.500
on the east side of the Nile
built by the Pharaoh Akhenaten

01:09:32.500 --> 01:09:36.090
and occupied for only 40 years.

01:09:36.090 --> 01:09:39.930
He had a religious argument
with the priest in Thebes

01:09:39.930 --> 01:09:43.350
and went across the Nile
to build his new town.

01:09:43.350 --> 01:09:51.479
The yellow in the plan
refers to the workers lair.

01:09:51.479 --> 01:09:55.140
There's another story,
which I haven't got time

01:09:55.140 --> 01:09:58.590
much to go into that.

01:09:58.590 --> 01:10:03.240
In Freud's writing
about Moses, the book

01:10:03.240 --> 01:10:06.220
is called Moses
and Monotheism, he

01:10:06.220 --> 01:10:11.580
talks about the connection
between pharaonic Egypt

01:10:11.580 --> 01:10:16.560
and the emergence of
Palestine, the sum notion

01:10:16.560 --> 01:10:21.550
that this land for Jerusalem
is taken from the Dead Sea

01:10:21.550 --> 01:10:22.050
Scrolls.

01:10:25.290 --> 01:10:31.230
The sum notion that there
was some connection passing

01:10:31.230 --> 01:10:34.260
on information
from the Jevasites,

01:10:34.260 --> 01:10:38.490
the first occupiers of
Jerusalem, or one of the first,

01:10:38.490 --> 01:10:40.410
and the Egyptians.

01:10:40.410 --> 01:10:40.910
Next.

01:10:43.920 --> 01:10:47.220
The Greek town, Miletus--

01:10:47.220 --> 01:10:49.600
Miletus, you can
see the structure

01:10:49.600 --> 01:10:50.850
of the containing wall.

01:10:54.080 --> 01:10:58.340
The orange and darker colors
of the imposition of the Romans

01:10:58.340 --> 01:11:00.440
on top of the Greek plan.

01:11:00.440 --> 01:11:02.750
Next.

01:11:02.750 --> 01:11:13.060
OK, Priene, the
main axes roads--

01:11:13.060 --> 01:11:17.500
again north-south with
minor roads east-west,

01:11:17.500 --> 01:11:23.350
and the central agora
complex and temple complex

01:11:23.350 --> 01:11:28.230
and part of the central
parts of the town.

01:11:28.230 --> 01:11:34.110
The Roman road system, an
extraordinary phenomenon.

01:11:34.110 --> 01:11:39.360
Just imagine at
the birth of Christ

01:11:39.360 --> 01:11:42.850
or a couple of hundred
years afterwards

01:11:42.850 --> 01:11:47.820
that there'd be an empire
built as significantly

01:11:47.820 --> 01:11:48.840
connected as this.

01:11:48.840 --> 01:11:54.000
This gives some indication
of the location of the Roman

01:11:54.000 --> 01:11:54.900
towns--

01:11:54.900 --> 01:11:59.215
5,627 according
to one authority.

01:11:59.215 --> 01:11:59.715
Next.

01:12:03.690 --> 01:12:07.710
castrametation, the
idea of the town

01:12:07.710 --> 01:12:11.550
as being cemented by
two connecting roads,

01:12:11.550 --> 01:12:17.220
a fortification
around the outskirts,

01:12:17.220 --> 01:12:22.140
and the notion of a
gridded system outside.

01:12:22.140 --> 01:12:25.680
It takes an enormous
amount of thought

01:12:25.680 --> 01:12:30.060
to imagine a town which
has a fortification having

01:12:30.060 --> 01:12:33.720
a counterpart formal
order outside the town.

01:12:33.720 --> 01:12:35.520
That is unique to the Romans.

01:12:35.520 --> 01:12:41.040
They were so conscious of
the clarity of the empire

01:12:41.040 --> 01:12:47.880
that they could imagine
making the land--

01:12:47.880 --> 01:12:53.670
again, the land as opposed to
the city in marks, the land

01:12:53.670 --> 01:12:55.980
as a friend of the city.

01:12:55.980 --> 01:12:58.668
Next.

01:12:58.668 --> 01:13:03.920
Here is the 6 by 6 system
of land subdivision

01:13:03.920 --> 01:13:10.520
for an ox which can
perambulate in one day

01:13:10.520 --> 01:13:18.010
the layout made by a [INAUDIBLE]
at the hands of a gromaticus.

01:13:18.010 --> 01:13:22.210
Here near [INAUDIBLE]
in Central Italy,

01:13:22.210 --> 01:13:27.620
you can see some of the effects
even today of the length

01:13:27.620 --> 01:13:31.890
of the centuriation pattern.

01:13:31.890 --> 01:13:36.570
The city is only in
existence in its relationship

01:13:36.570 --> 01:13:43.110
to this space outside it as it
is condensed in its interior.

01:13:43.110 --> 01:13:44.470
It's a phenomenal idea.

01:13:46.990 --> 01:13:50.070
It's an idea which
American cities have not,

01:13:50.070 --> 01:13:54.370
or modern cities, have
not understood completely.

01:13:54.370 --> 01:13:54.870
Next.

01:13:57.740 --> 01:14:03.920
Timgad, the great Roman city
for veterans on North Africa.

01:14:03.920 --> 01:14:07.220
The Cardo and Decumanus
here are shortened

01:14:07.220 --> 01:14:11.280
because of the location of the
forum and the amphitheater.

01:14:11.280 --> 01:14:11.780
Next.

01:14:14.860 --> 01:14:20.800
Two plans-- Verona on the
right and the first attempt

01:14:20.800 --> 01:14:29.830
in a relatively Renaissance plan
of Florence based on attempts

01:14:29.830 --> 01:14:33.040
to introduce a local
taxation system

01:14:33.040 --> 01:14:36.305
and still respecting
the Roman grid.

01:14:36.305 --> 01:14:36.805
Next.

01:14:39.920 --> 01:14:42.500
The southwest of France--

01:14:42.500 --> 01:14:45.390
the Bastide town,
a pair of towns.

01:14:45.390 --> 01:14:48.540
The cornier in the center,
the church on the side.

01:14:48.540 --> 01:14:49.040
Next.

01:14:51.896 --> 01:14:56.230
[SPEAKING FRENCH] Here you
see something interesting

01:14:56.230 --> 01:14:57.700
geometrically.

01:14:57.700 --> 01:15:02.010
The blocks as they go
further from the center

01:15:02.010 --> 01:15:05.140
have the horizontal length
based on the diagonal

01:15:05.140 --> 01:15:07.120
of the previous.

01:15:07.120 --> 01:15:11.335
So the blocks get
bigger as you go out.

01:15:11.335 --> 01:15:13.992
It's a geometric trick.

01:15:13.992 --> 01:15:16.730
Here it is.

01:15:16.730 --> 01:15:19.430
Next.

01:15:19.430 --> 01:15:26.120
[INAUDIBLE] the great
town on the Mediterranean,

01:15:26.120 --> 01:15:27.980
clearly in prismatic.

01:15:27.980 --> 01:15:30.290
This served is one
of the launching

01:15:30.290 --> 01:15:37.370
points for many crusades
to Christianize Jerusalem.

