And here's [INAUDIBLE]
one of the roads running

01:15:41.450 --> 01:15:44.660
through the central
plaza, a cornier

01:15:44.660 --> 01:15:49.190
system of creating
a greater pedestrian

01:15:49.190 --> 01:15:51.830
opportunity in the center.

01:15:51.830 --> 01:15:56.325
It's like building a permanent
arcade around the center.

01:15:56.325 --> 01:15:56.825
Next.

01:15:59.630 --> 01:16:02.060
Here's the Meridian
of Tordesillas--

01:16:02.060 --> 01:16:05.690
the Spanish world and
the North American world.

01:16:05.690 --> 01:16:09.020
Here's a typical Laws
of the Indies town.

01:16:09.020 --> 01:16:12.930
I think it's Caracas
central plaza.

01:16:12.930 --> 01:16:13.430
Next.

01:16:17.860 --> 01:16:25.060
In contrast, the development
of the typical Portuguese town,

01:16:25.060 --> 01:16:28.180
as you can see from
its early stages,

01:16:28.180 --> 01:16:31.025
has developed long strips.

01:16:31.025 --> 01:16:31.525
Next.

01:16:35.560 --> 01:16:40.580
Again, this is-- thank you.

01:16:40.580 --> 01:16:44.000
This is a thesis done
on examining the Laws

01:16:44.000 --> 01:16:46.380
of the Indies in detail.

01:16:46.380 --> 01:16:52.310
It's a thesis here at MIT
by Guillermo Frontado.

01:16:52.310 --> 01:16:56.900
He looks at the
streets at the plazas

01:16:56.900 --> 01:17:00.260
and interprets the
laws in formal terms--

01:17:00.260 --> 01:17:05.055
what distances they occupy,
what sections they produce,

01:17:05.055 --> 01:17:06.630
and so on.

01:17:06.630 --> 01:17:07.130
Next.

01:17:10.720 --> 01:17:14.020
So here is the
subsequent development

01:17:14.020 --> 01:17:19.960
of two central capital
Latin American cities based

01:17:19.960 --> 01:17:21.130
on the Laws of the Indies.

01:17:21.130 --> 01:17:25.660
Here are the major churches
on the central plaza.

01:17:25.660 --> 01:17:30.940
Here you see the adaptation
of the central plaza

01:17:30.940 --> 01:17:35.440
theme in subsequent
decentralized plazas.

01:17:35.440 --> 01:17:35.940
Next.

01:17:42.390 --> 01:17:49.260
Subdivision of the 6
by 6 mile 1785 system.

01:17:49.260 --> 01:17:49.760
Next.

01:17:52.630 --> 01:17:57.610
Salt Lake City,
Harrington, Kansas--

01:17:57.610 --> 01:17:59.540
built the railway company.

01:17:59.540 --> 01:18:00.040
Next.

01:18:04.790 --> 01:18:08.720
Chicago, which we'll deal
with in some detail later on.

01:18:08.720 --> 01:18:16.400
And Burnham's Plan
1907, 1905 Plan

01:18:16.400 --> 01:18:23.250
to centralize the
grid of Chicago.

01:18:23.250 --> 01:18:28.380
It's an extraordinary
plan, diagonalizing

01:18:28.380 --> 01:18:31.740
the grid towards the center.

01:18:31.740 --> 01:18:35.905
It's kind of attempt
cosmetize Chicago.

01:18:35.905 --> 01:18:36.405
Next.

01:18:39.650 --> 01:18:43.490
1811 Plan.

01:18:43.490 --> 01:18:46.280
Again, this is out of focus.

01:18:46.280 --> 01:18:48.740
Now, why then change this.

01:18:48.740 --> 01:18:54.060
The story of Central
Park is another story.

01:18:54.060 --> 01:18:55.280
Next.

01:18:55.280 --> 01:19:00.410
The inevitable connections
of the east and west,

01:19:00.410 --> 01:19:04.280
maintaining the grid,
while still producing

01:19:04.280 --> 01:19:06.870
a major public garden.

01:19:06.870 --> 01:19:07.370
Next.

01:19:10.330 --> 01:19:18.310
The cattaneo model-- that
is, dispersing open space

01:19:18.310 --> 01:19:22.180
throughout the system and
having different widths of roads

01:19:22.180 --> 01:19:23.710
is part of the system.

01:19:23.710 --> 01:19:24.730
Next.

01:19:24.730 --> 01:19:32.150
Savannah, Georgia--
still a marvelous town,

01:19:32.150 --> 01:19:35.610
and a town which resisted here.

01:19:35.610 --> 01:19:38.720
There's a book called
the Night of Garden.

01:19:38.720 --> 01:19:39.890
What's the book?

01:19:39.890 --> 01:19:43.600
Anybody know the book?

01:19:43.600 --> 01:19:47.680
Which talks about
Savannah's decision

01:19:47.680 --> 01:19:52.300
not to take large companies,
like insurance companies

01:19:52.300 --> 01:19:55.090
as headquarters because
of their attempt

01:19:55.090 --> 01:19:57.260
to keep the local system.

01:19:57.260 --> 01:19:57.760
Next.

01:20:00.390 --> 01:20:02.540
And a few of the
modern examples.

01:20:02.540 --> 01:20:05.250
This is Soria y Mata,
the Spaniard's plan

01:20:05.250 --> 01:20:12.420
for linearizing the outskirts
of Madrid, a linear model being

01:20:12.420 --> 01:20:15.630
a very popular model,
taken essentially

01:20:15.630 --> 01:20:18.715
from a mass fabrication system.

01:20:18.715 --> 01:20:19.215
Next.

01:20:21.870 --> 01:20:29.670
[INAUDIBLE] the affirming
steed, the magnificent steed,

