And the Ascoral Plan,
which Corbusier was one of,

01:20:42.570 --> 01:20:51.880
1940, a plan to link
Europe, to linearize Europe.

01:20:51.880 --> 01:20:52.380
Next.

01:20:56.420 --> 01:21:00.740
Captain [? Chambliss's ?]
plan for linking New York

01:21:00.740 --> 01:21:08.510
and Washington with a
public train system that

01:21:08.510 --> 01:21:10.400
had an effect on
the local-- that

01:21:10.400 --> 01:21:15.020
fed off the agricultural
land next to it.

01:21:15.020 --> 01:21:19.340
Somebody called it a
horizontal skyscraper.

01:21:19.340 --> 01:21:24.860
Kenzo Tange's 1960 plan
for the linearizing Tokyo

01:21:24.860 --> 01:21:28.820
and creating a greater use
of the harbor, of the water.

01:21:28.820 --> 01:21:31.630
Next.

01:21:31.630 --> 01:21:38.500
Stupid plans like this by Jonah
Friedman to linearize Paris.

01:21:38.500 --> 01:21:41.470
Absolute madness--
should lock people up.

01:21:45.680 --> 01:21:46.180
Next.

01:21:49.880 --> 01:21:53.930
The fascination with
bringing together

01:21:53.930 --> 01:21:56.570
a number of mechanical forces--

01:21:56.570 --> 01:22:03.590
train, bus, pedestrian,
and the many schemas

01:22:03.590 --> 01:22:09.710
for maximizing
density in New York.

01:22:09.710 --> 01:22:14.840
The stupidity of the
Archigram proposal for moving.

01:22:14.840 --> 01:22:18.770
Archigram would have
worked very well in Egypt

01:22:18.770 --> 01:22:21.830
where you had no investment
in permanent sites,

01:22:21.830 --> 01:22:23.660
but you moved around.

01:22:23.660 --> 01:22:27.530
This is the grasshopper
city, which moves around.

01:22:27.530 --> 01:22:29.870
If there's anything we've
learned historically,

01:22:29.870 --> 01:22:34.790
that the inertia of
cities in modern times

01:22:34.790 --> 01:22:37.670
maintains this position.

01:22:37.670 --> 01:22:41.870
I've said this before, that you
can count the number of cities.

01:22:41.870 --> 01:22:44.360
There are cities in
trouble like Detroit,

01:22:44.360 --> 01:22:49.460
but there's no disappearance
of cities, or very few,

01:22:49.460 --> 01:22:52.455
compared to previous times.

01:22:52.455 --> 01:22:52.955
Next.

01:22:56.980 --> 01:23:00.300
It's called Buckminster
Fuller and notion

01:23:00.300 --> 01:23:04.230
of using a single
machine to cover

01:23:04.230 --> 01:23:06.760
the whole of the
city of Manhattan.

01:23:06.760 --> 01:23:07.260
Next.

01:23:10.540 --> 01:23:12.710
I think we end here.

01:23:12.710 --> 01:23:15.400
This is Lord
Behrens' proposition

01:23:15.400 --> 01:23:18.610
for the AEG factory--

01:23:18.610 --> 01:23:21.760
just about done--
in Berlin showing

01:23:21.760 --> 01:23:27.340
the wonderful correct place
for every worker in the system.

01:23:27.340 --> 01:23:36.130
And here the nightmare of Soweto
outside Johannesburg, or part

01:23:36.130 --> 01:23:40.240
of Johannesburg,
where race created

01:23:40.240 --> 01:23:47.290
a new town in which the
machine model is exemplified

01:23:47.290 --> 01:23:50.470
par excellence
with no pretension

01:23:50.470 --> 01:23:55.630
paid to anything else but
the disposition of houses

01:23:55.630 --> 01:23:57.800
in free space.

01:23:57.800 --> 01:23:59.350
OK.